Mr Odinga has abandoned his previous stand, even “advising” health care workers to respect the oath they took.Mr Odinga and Dr Ruto are not the only ones in the doublespeak boat. Immediately seven doctors’ union officials were released by the courts for leading what would become a 100-day work boycott, Orange Democratic Movement boss Raila Odinga led the opposition in a mid-morning rally at Uhuru Park.
The date was February 26, 2017 and the rally was celebratory since the union officials had just been freed from jail. They vowed to push on with their demands.



